# Reading Understanding

depends on:

```text id="m4r2qe"
meaning-making
and
text reasoning
```

Theme and main idea are NOT:

```text id="r7r5qe"
same thing
```

Students learn:

```text id="x2r8qe"
read text
→ identify important details
→ determine main idea
→ infer theme
→ explain evidence
```

This develops:

* comprehension
* inference
* evidence use
* reasoning
* literary understanding

This becomes:

# Meaning Thinking

Common misconceptions:

children may believe:

```text id="p6r1qe"
theme
=
topic
```

or:

```text id="u3r9qe"
main idea
=
single detail
```

Some may:

```text id="c8r4qe"
choose
favorite part
instead of
central meaning
```

without understanding:

```text id="k5r7qe"
main idea
and
theme
require
evidence
```

Example:

students may say:

Story:

```text id="n1r6qe"
about friendship
```

Theme:

```text id="t9r2qe"
friendship
```

instead of recognizing:

```text id="q4r8qe"
friendship
can help
solve problems
```

This skill teaches:

```text id="v7r3qe"
evidence-based meaning
```

For Grade 4:

focus includes:

Main Idea:

* central message of text
* supporting details
* nonfiction understanding

Theme:

* lesson or message
* inference
* literary interpretation

Important distinction:

```text id="a2r5qe"
topic
=
subject

main idea
=
what text says

theme
=
life lesson
or message
```

